@node intro "Introduction"

@{b}·Introduction@{ub}

Long time ago, one of my Amiga m8 ask me for litte program
that allow him to have a randomized name of ram-disk instead
of normal 'ram disk'

I made him a first version, and after some time I relased update
Now its time to finish this thread :-)

more info:@{"History" link histo}

@endnode

@node sysrq "System req."

@{b}·System Req.@{ub}

All u need is

- Amiga with kickstart 2.04+
- relebel command somewere in path
- imagination (for ramdisk names:)

@endnode

@node usage "Usage"

@{b}·Usage & Instalation@{ub}

Instalation - simpli copy @{fg fill}rr@{fg text} file somewhere
in path (c: will be best option)

Usage - edit one of Yours startup files,find best place
        (in your opinion of course) and put somethink like
        this

<example startup-sequene>

run >nil: newicons
run >nil: beterobtainpens
run >nil: visualprefs

;this is important!!!!
rr My_Khul_Ram AmigaNG POWERPC This_Is_A_Ram
;ok? :-)

loadwb quiet
endcli

so, all You need to do is put rr somewhere and pass some names
for Yours ramdisk....

@endnode

@node futur "Future"

@{b}·Future@{ub}

Well, there is not much left :-)

I got on my hdd new version of rr but it will be a whole
new story! Its using commodities.library, and some asm
routines for cleaning Your ram....
So, just You w8 m8 :P
@endnode

